main event: A civilian reported seeing three unidentified flying objects over Clyde, New York, on August 6, 1967.
interesting points: The witness observed the objects for approximately 5 minutes and noted they were circular in shape, emitting a white light., The objects were estimated to be 30 to 40 feet in diameter., No sound was associated with the objects during the sighting., The local police department was notified, and the report was passed on to the Air Force., The Air Force investigation concluded that the phenomenon was likely conventional aircraft reflecting light but could not identify them as such.
witness description: The witness, who wishes to remain anonymous, reported seeing the objects while driving along Rte. 414 and was a lifelong resident of the area.
